Yep, agreed. I removed `render_task_config_env` and force-pushed a cleaner PR update: [#10699](https://github.com/jdx/mise/pull/10699).

New shape: monorepo subproject task discovery now renders tasks with a scoped config built from that subproject’s config hierarchy, so `Task::tera_ctx()` stays boring and doesn’t manually resolve/apply env.

Verified with:

- `cargo fmt`
- `cargo check -q`
- `mise run test:e2e e2e/tasks/test_task_ls_complete_monorepo`

The unrelated workflow files are still dirty in the worktree.

::git-stage{cwd="/Users/jdx/.codex/worktrees/045e/mise"}
::git-commit{cwd="/Users/jdx/.codex/worktrees/045e/mise"}
::git-push{cwd="/Users/jdx/.codex/worktrees/045e/mise" branch="codex/fix-monorepo-task-env-render"}

